{
  "name": "Iron Bands of Binding",
  "type": "equipment",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"ddb\">\n<p>This rusty iron &amp;Reference[sphere]{sphere} measures 3 inches in diameter and weighs 1 pound. You can use an action to speak the command word and throw the &amp;Reference[sphere]{sphere} at a Huge or smaller creature you can see within 60 feet of you. As the &amp;Reference[sphere]{sphere} moves through the air, it opens into a tangle of metal bands.</p>\n<p>Make a ranged attack roll with an attack bonus equal to your &amp;Reference[dex]{Dexterity} modifier plus your proficiency bonus. On a hit, the target is &amp;Reference[restrained]{restrained} until you take a bonus action to speak the command word again to release it. Doing so, or missing with the attack, causes the bands to contract and become a &amp;Reference[sphere]{sphere} once more.</p>\n<p>A creature, including the one &amp;Reference[restrained]{restrained}, can use an action to make a DC 20 &amp;Reference[str]{Strength} check to break the iron bands. On a success, the item is destroyed, and the &amp;Reference[restrained]{restrained} creature is freed. If the check fails, any further attempts made by that creature automatically fail until 24 hours have elapsed.</p>\n<p>Once the bands are used, they can't be used again until the next dawn.</p>\n</div>",
      "chat": ""
    },
